div.h2: Why Skip Connections Prevent Gradient Vanishing in Deep Transformers

div.p: Residual connections were first introduced for computer vision networks. The same insight applies to transformers:

ul.li: Without skip: Deep networks are harder to train than shallow ones
With skip: Deep networks can match shallow network performance + learn residual

div.p: The "highway" allows gradients to bypass vanishing-prone layers entirely. Each layer learns a residual correction to the identity function.
x = x + F(x) where F is attention + FFN
L/x = L/x (1 + F/x) L/x 1 (the +1 is the highway!)

p.strong: Result: L/x L/x 1.0 all layers learn!
